    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="886"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2057</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Swedish Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EWAF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ekengren</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 18th ultimo,<note n="1" xml:id="d886fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_616">p. 616</ref>.</note> in
                    which you advise me that you have been instructed by the Royal Government of
                    Sweden to communicate to me certain observations made by the Royal Swedish
                    Government regarding a note addressed by the Government of the United States to
                    the Government of Great Britain on November 5 last, concerning the matter of the
                    interference by belligerents with neutral commerce and navigation.</p>
                <p>Due note has been taken by the Government of the United States of the
                    observations made by the Royal Swedish Government.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
